'''Arrowhead Pawn Shop''' is a [[pawn shop]] and part of the [[Iron Pipeline]].<ref name=NYT-trace>{{cite web|last1=Blinder|first1=Alan|last2=Baker|first2=Al|last3=Goodman|first3=David|title=Tracing the Gun Used to Kill 2 New York City Police Officers|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2014/12/25/nyregion/tracing-the-gun-used-to-kill-2-new-york-city-police-officers.html?_r=0|website=|newspaper=[[The New York Times]]|accessdate=7 May 2015}}</ref> It was founded in 1991 and is located in [[Jonesboro, Georgia]].<ref name="founded">{{cite web |url=http://listings.findthecompany.com/l/18621913/Arrowhead-Pawn-And-Gun-Shop-Inc |title=Arrowhead Pawn & Gun Shop Inc |publisher=FindTheCompany |accessdate=September 25, 2017}}</ref> The store was described as the most significant source outside of New York State of guns recovered by the New York Police Department in 2009.<ref name=NYT-trace/><ref name=NYD-shop>{{cite web|last1=Kemp|first1=Joe|last2=Parascandola|first2=Rocca|last3=McShane|first3=Larry|title=Little Shop of Horror: Georgia store Arrowhead Pawn sold nine guns that made their way to New York|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/news/crime/shop-horror-georgia-store-arrowhead-pawn-sold-guns-made-new-york-article-1.181634#bmb=1|website=|newspaper=[[Daily News (New York)|New York Daily News]]|accessdate=7 May 2015}}</ref> After a gun from the shop was used in [[2014 killings of NYPD officers|the murders]] of two [[New York City Police Department]] (NYPD) officers, the ''[[New York Times]]'' reported that Arrowhead ranked fifth on the U.S.-wide list of legal sources of guns used in crimes.<ref name=NYT-trace/> The newspaper quoted an anonymous federal official as stating that "[Arrowhead] were like a [[Crazy Eddie]] of gun dealers. They had a lot of volume and they did a lot of business."<ref name=NYT-trace/> The [[Brady Center to Prevent Gun Violence]] describes Arrowhead as a "notorious 'bad apple' gun dealer", having sold over 1720 guns that were subsequently used in crimes.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bradycampaign.org/press-room/beyond-the-gun-trace-holding-%E2%80%98bad-apple%E2%80%99-gun-dealers-accountable|publisher=Brady Center to Prevent Gun Violence|title=Beyond the gun trace|date=24 December 2014}}</ref>
Arrowhead Pawn Shop was rebuilt in 2007 following a fire; retail space quadrupled from 2,000 square feet to 8,000 square feet in the new premises.<ref name=Arrowhead>{{cite web|title=Arrowhead Pawn Premier Atlanta Pawn Shop|url=http://www.arrowheadpawn.com/|publisher=Arrowhead Pawn Shop|accessdate=7 May 2015}}</ref> As of 2014, the store's chief executive is Arthur Banks.<ref name=NYT-trace/> The shop describes itself as "a family owned business dedicated to good prices, good customer service and good vibes".<ref name=Arrowhead/>
